{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"USN-6657-1","published":"2024-02-26T13:52:13.956982Z","modified":"2025-10-13T04:36:47Z","related":["UBUNTU-CVE-2023-28450","UBUNTU-CVE-2023-50387","UBUNTU-CVE-2023-50868"],"upstream":["CVE-2023-28450","CVE-2023-50387","CVE-2023-50868","UBUNTU-CVE-2023-28450","UBUNTU-CVE-2023-50387","UBUNTU-CVE-2023-50868"],"summary":"dnsmasq vulnerabilities","details":"Elias Heftrig, Haya Schulmann, Niklas Vogel, and Michael Waidner discovered\nthat Dnsmasq icorrectly handled validating DNSSEC messages. A remote\nattacker could possibly use this issue to cause Dnsmasq to consume\nresources, leading to a denial of service. (CVE-2023-50387)\n\nIt was discovered that Dnsmasq incorrectly handled preparing an NSEC3\nclosest encloser proof. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to\ncause Dnsmasq to consume resources, leading to a denial of service.\n(CVE-2023-50868)\n\nIt was discovered that Dnsmasq incorrectly set the maximum EDNS.0 UDP\npacket size as required by DNS Flag Day 2020. This issue only affected\nUbuntu 23.10. (CVE-2023-28450)\n","affected":[{"package":{"name":"dnsmasq","ecosystem":"Ubuntu:20.04:LTS","purl":"pkg:deb/ubuntu/dnsmasq@2.90-0ubuntu0.20.04.1?arch=source&distro=focal"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"2.90-0ubuntu0.20.04.1"}]}],"versions":["2.80-1ubuntu2","2.80-1ubuntu4","2.80-1.1ubuntu1","2.80-1.1ubuntu1.2","2.80-1.1ubuntu1.3","2.80-1.1ubuntu1.4","2.80-1.1ubuntu1.5","2.80-1.1ubuntu1.6","2.80-1.1ubuntu1.7"],"ecosystem_specific":{"availability":"No subscription required","binaries":[{"binary_name":"dnsmasq","binary_version":"2.90-0ubuntu0.20.04.1"},{"binary_name":"dnsmasq-base","binary_version":"2.90-0ubuntu0.20.04.1"},{"binary_name":"dnsmasq-base-lua","binary_version":"2.90-0ubuntu0.20.04.1"},{"binary_name":"dnsmasq-utils","binary_version":"2.90-0ubuntu0.20.04.1"}]},"database_specific":{"cves_map":{"cves":[{"id":"CVE-2023-50387","severity":[{"score":"CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I: